Game select
===========
 Up&Down Arrow/      : Move marker from game to game
 Joystick up/down
 ENTER/ Fire 1 button: Choose game to play. Note that you can only play
                       games whose name isn't displayed in dark green.
 ESC                 : Exit to DOS
 L                   : Load a previously saved gamed position
 S                   : Save current game position
 F1                  : Help screen
 F2                  : Toggle Sound

 NOTE: You do have eight "slots" for saving your game positions to. These
       slots correspond to the eight filenames savegame.1, savegame.2, ...
       savegame.8. You can free one slot simply by deleting the appropriate
       file, for example
         del savegame.4       (from DOS-prompt)
       would free the 4th slot.
       You can move a savegame from one slot to another by renaming it, for
       example
         ren savegame.2 savegame.5
       would move the second slotentry to the fifth. This may be useful if
       you want to exchange savegames with a friend.




Keyboard controls during the game
=================================
 Arrow-keys          : move the player
 CTRL+arrow-keys     : dig into the specified directions without changing
                       the players position
 ESC                 : cancel the actual game
 SPACE               : Game pause

Joystick controls during the game
=================================
 move stick into either direction in order to move (what have you guessed?)
 Hold Fire 2 button and move to dig into the specified directions without
 changing your position.




