Problems with the joystick
 If the player sometimes still moves although the button 2 is pressed
 you probably have a joystick with auto-fire. Usually there is a switch
 to turn this off...

Playing BASH when Windows is running
 You may run BASH fullscreen in Windows but on my slow PC scrolling is not
 that smooth when Windows is active and when the DOS-task is running in the
 background. If you have the same problem close Windows and try playing
 BASH again.

If you run into trouble please consider that I have only tested the game on
a limited number of computers. I just don't have enough money to by all
types of VGA-cards in order to test if my game works with them. The same
thing holds for operating systems, bus-systems and joysticks.

One great problem may be the speed of your computer. I developed BASH
on a 386/40 and it was fast enough. I haven't found a slower PC around here
so I cannot say if it works on slower PCs. If your computer is slower the
graphics may be not that smooth.

